{"title_page": "Quezon City's 1st congressional district", "text_new": "{{Infobox constituency\n|name = Quezon City's 1st congressional district\n|parl_name = [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]]\n|image = Quezon City 1st District.svg\n|caption = Boundary of Quezon City's 1st congressional district in [[Quezon City]]\n|image2 = <!-- insert locator map of city/province here -->\n|caption2 = <!-- Location of city/province within the [[Philippines]] -->\n|district_label = City\n|district = [[Quezon City]]\n|region_label = Region\n|region = [[Metro Manila]]\n|population = 409,162<ref name=\":0\">https://psa.gov.ph/sites/default/files/attachments/hsd/pressrelease/2015_Table%201_Legislative%20Districts.xlsx</ref>\n|electorate = 184,554 (2016)<ref name=\"comelec\">{{cite web|url=https://www.comelec.gov.ph/php-tpls-attachments/2016NLE/Statistics/Philippine2016VotersProfile/Philippine_2016_Voter_Profile_by_Provinces_and_Cities_or_Municipalities_including_Districts.xlsx |title=Philippines 2016 Voters Profile |publisher=[[Commission on Elections (Philippines)]] |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n|area = {{convert|19.59|sqkm|sqmi|abbr=on}}\n|towns = {{Collapsible list\n| titlestyle = font-weight:normal;text-align:left;background-color:WhiteSmoke;\n| title = Several barangays\n| Alicia, [[Bagong Pag-asa]], Bahay Toro, Balingasa, [[Bungad]], Damar, Damayan, Del Monte, Katipunan, Lourdes, Maharlika, Manresa, Mariblo, Masambong, N.S. Amoranto (Gintong Silahis), Nayong Kanluran, Paang Bundok, Pag-ibig sa Nayon, Paltok, Paraiso, Phil-Am, Project 6, Ramon Magsaysay, Saint Peter, Salvacion, San Antonio, San Isidro Labrador, San Jose, [[Santa Cruz, Quezon City|Santa Cruz]], Santa Teresita, Santo Cristo, Santo Domingo, Siena, Talayan, Vasra, [[Veterans Village]], West Triangle\n}}\n|year = 1987\n|members_label = Representative\n|members = [[Anthony Peter Crisologo]]\n|blank1_name = Political party\n|blank1_info = {{Color box|{{National Unity Party (Philippines)/meta/color}}|border=darkgray}} [[National Unity Party (Philippines)|NUP]]\n|blank2_name = Congressional bloc\n|blank2_info = Majority\n}}\n'''Quezon City's 6th congressional district''' is one of the six [[congressional districts of the Philippines]] in [[Quezon City]]. It has been represented in the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] since 1987.<ref name=\"congleg\">{{cite web|url=http://www.congress.gov.ph/legislators/?v=province |title=Roster of Philippine legislators |publisher=[[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref> The district consists of the eastern barangays bordering Manila and the southern exclave of Caloocan.<ref name=\"apportion\">{{cite web|url=https://www.chanrobles.com/ordinance.htm |title=The 1987 Constitution of the Republic of the Philippines |publisher=Chan Robles Virtual Law Library |accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref> It is currently represented in the [[18th Congress of the Philippines|18th Congress]] by [[Anthony Peter Crisologo]] of the [[National Unity Party (Philippines)|National Unity Party]] (NUP).<ref name=\"congmem\">{{cite web|url=http://www.congress.gov.ph/members/ |title=House Members |publisher=[[House of Representatives of the Philippines]] |accessdate=20 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Representation history==\n{| class=wikitable \n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | #\n! rowspan=\"2\" colspan=2 | Member\n! colspan=2 | Term of office\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Congress\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Party\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Electoral history\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Constituent<br/>[[Local government in the Philippines|LGU]]s\n|-\n!Start!!End\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\" |\n\n===Quezon City's 1st district for the [[House of Representatives of the Philippines]]===\n|-\n| colspan=\"9\" style=\"text-align:center;\" | District created February 2, 1987.<ref name=\"apportion\"/>\n|-\n|rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''1'''\n|rowspan=2|\n|rowspan=2| Renato A. Yap\n|rowspan=2| June 30, 1987\n|rowspan=2| June 30, 1992\