y|Nacionalista]]\n| [[2004 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 2004]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[14th Congress of the Philippines|14th]]\n| [[2007 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Re-elected in 2007]].\n|-\n| style=\"background:{{United Nationalist Alliance/meta/color}};\" |\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[15th Congress of the Philippines|15th]]\n| [[United Nationalist Alliance|UNA]]\n| [[2010 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Re-elected in 2010]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''4'''\n| style=\"background:{{Liberal Party (Philippines)/meta/color}};\" |\n| [[Francisco Boy Calalay]]\n| June 30, 2013\n| June 30, 2016\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[16th Congress of the Philippines|16th]]\n| [[Liberal Party (Philippines)|Liberal]]\n| [[2013 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 2013]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | ''(2)''\n| style=\"background:{{Partido Demokratiko Pilipino-Lakas ng Bayan/meta/color}};\" |\n| [[Vincente Crisologo]]\n| June 30, 2016\n| June 30, 2019\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[17th Congress of the Philippines|17th]]\n| [[PDP\u2013Laban]]\n| [[2016 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 2016]].\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | '''5'''\n| style=\"background:{{National Unity Party (Philippines)/meta/color}};\"|\n| [[Anthony Peter Crisologo]]\n| June 30, 2019\n| Incumbent\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" | [[18th Congress of the Philippines|18th]]\n| [[National Unity Party (Philippines)|NUP]]\n| [[2019 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Elected in 2019]].\n|}\n\n==Election results==\n\n{{Election box begin no change | title=[[2010 Philippine House of Representatives elections|Philippine House of Representatives election at Quezon City's 1st district]]}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Nacionalista Party\n  |candidate  = [[Vincent \"Bingbong\" Crisologo]]\n  |votes     