a]]\n*[[List of earthquakes in Haiti]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n'''Sources'''\n{{refbegin}}\n*{{citation|title=Significant Earthquake Database|url=https://www.ngdc.noaa.gov/nndc/struts/form?t=101650&s=1&d=1|author=NGDC|publisher=[[National Geophysical Data Center]], [[National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration|NOAA]]|doi=10.7289/V5TD9V7K}}\n{{refend}}\n\n{{Earthquakes in the Caribbean}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of earthquakes|Caribbean]]\n[[Category:Caribbean geology-related lists|Earthquakes]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{More citations needed|date=January 2020}}\n\nMajor '''earthquakes in the Caribbean''' are infrequent and are sometimes accompanied by tsunami.\n\n==Earthquakes==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!Date\n!Region\n!{{m|Mag}}\n![[Mercalli intensity scale|MMI]]\n!Deaths\n!Injuries\n!Comments\n! Source\n|-\n|[[2020 Jamaica earthquake|2020-01-28]] || Jamaica, Cuba, Cayman Islands || 7.7 {{M|w|link=y}} || VI ||  || || 0.3-1 meter tsunami ||\n|-\n|[[2020 Puerto Rico earthquakes|2020-01-20]] || Puerto Rico || 6.4 {{M|w|link=y}} || VIII || 4 || 9 || || ||\n|-\n| [[2018 Haiti earthquake|2018-10-07]] || Port-de-Paix || 5.9 {{M|w|link=y}} || V || 18 || 580 || ||\n|-\n|[[August 2018 Venezuela earthquakes|2018-08-21]] || Venezuela, Trinidad || 7.3 {{M|w|link=y}} || VII || 5 || 122 || || \n|-\n| [[2010 Haiti earthquake|2010-01-12]] || Port-au-Prince || 7.0 {{M|w|link=y}} || IX || 100,000\u2013316,000 || 300,000 || Extreme damage / tsunami || \n|-\n|[[2007 Martinique earthquake|2007-11-29]]|| Martinique || 7.4 {{M|w|link=y}}|| VI\u2013VII|| 6 || 402 ||  || \n|-\n| [[2004 Les Saintes earthquake|2004-11-21]] || Guadeloupe, Dominica || 6.3 {{M|w|link=y}} || VII || 1 || 13 || Non-destructive tsunami || \n|-\n| [[2003 Dominican Republic earthquake|2003-09-22]] || Dominican Republic || 6.4 {{M|w|link=y}} || VII || 3 || || || \n|-\n|1997-04-22\n|Trinidad and Tobago\n|6.7 {{M|w|link=y}}\n|