{"title_page": "Jackson Rathbone", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n|name = Jackson Rathbone\n|image = JacksonRathbone10TIFF.jpg\t\n|caption = Rathbone at the [[2010 Toronto International Film Festival]]\n|birth_name = Monroe Jackson Rathbone V\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|12|14}}\n| residence = [[Los Angeles, California]]\n|birth_place = [[Singapore]]\n|occupation = Actor, musician\n|years_active = 2005\u2013present\n|spouse = {{marriage|Sheila Hafsadi|September 29, 2013}}'''Born:''' {{birth date and age|1987|1|8}}\n|children = Monroe Rathbone, VI, (son)<br />'''Born:''' {{birth date and age|2012|7|5}}<br />Presley Rathbone, (daughter)<br />'''Born:''' {{birth date and age|2016|5|31}}<br />Felix Rathbone, (son)<br />'''Born:''' {{birth date and age|2019|12|31}}\n|relatives = [[Monroe Jackson Rathbone II]]\n}}\n\n'''Monroe Jackson Rathbone V'''<ref>{{cite web|title=For Jackson Rathbone, this could be heartthrob breakout week|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/entertainment/20100630_Charge_.html|website=[[The Philadelphia Inquirer]]|accessdate=July 3, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Faran Krentcil |title=Jackson Rathbone: Uncut |url=http://www.nylonmag.com/?section=article&parid=4697 |publisher=Nylon Holding Inc. |work=Nylon magazine |date=2010-06-03 |accessdate=2010-06-04 }}</ref> (born December 14, 1984)<ref>{{cite web|title=Hello! Meet the band & more monkeys|url=http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/band/ |publisher=100 Monkeys |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110707054255/http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/band/ |archivedate=July 7, 2011 |accessdate=2012-07-09}}</ref> is an American [[actor]] and [[musician]] known for his role as [[Jasper Hale]] in [[The Twilight Saga (film series)|''The Twilight Saga'' series]].\n\n==Early life==\nRathbone was born in [[Singapore]], the son of American parents Randee Lynn (n\u00e9e Brauner) and Monroe Jackson Rathbone IV. He has three sisters, including ceramic artist Kelly Rathbone.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://kellyrathbone.com/ | title=Kelly Garrett Rathbone \"Lost Mariposas\" | accessdate=August 4, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"ref11223\">{{cite news|last=Collins|first=Catherine|title=\"Twilight\" Star's Midland Roots|pages=|publisher=[[KOSA-TV|CBS 7 News]]|date=2009-11-19|url=http://www.cbs7.com/news/details.asp?ID=16288|accessdate=2009-11-22}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref name=\"ref1122\">{{cite news|title=Randee Lynn Brauner and Monroe Jackson Rathbone IV married...|pages=|newspaper=[[Midland Reporter-Telegram]]|date=2007-01-18|url=http://nl.newsbank.com/nl-search/we/Archives?p_product=MRTB&p_theme=mrtb&p_action=search&p_maxdocs=200&p_topdoc=1&p_text_direct-0=116BCCFAF8E746A8&p_field_direct-0=document_id&p_perpage=10&p_sort=YMD_date:D&s_trackval=GooglePM|accessdate=2009-11-22}}</ref> \n\nRathbone is distantly related to Civil War general [[Stonewall Jackson]] and British actor [[Basil Rathbone]].<ref name=eni>{{cite news|last=Baker|first=Tom|title='Airbender' ideal: Sweet but strong|pages=|publisher=Daily Yomiuri Online|date=2010-07-16|url=http://www.yomiuri.co.jp/dy/features/arts/20100716TDY12T04.htm|accessdate=2010-07-20}}</ref> His great-grandfather, [[Monroe Jackson Rathbone II]], was the chairman of Standard Oil of New Jersey, which later became [[Exxon]].<ref name=\"ref1122\"/> Because of his father's job at [[Mobil]] Oil, Rathbone has lived in many places including [[Norway]], [[Indonesia]], and [[Midland, Texas]].<ref name=\"bio\">{{cite web|url=http://www.prayformorningmovie.com/cast/jackson-rathbone.php|work=Pray for Morning movie|title=Jackson Rathbone|accessdate=2008-02-15|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20060819100704/http://www.prayformorningmovie.com/cast/jackson-rathbone.php|archivedate=2006-08-19}}</ref> \n\nHe attended Trinity School of Midland and started out in local theater in Midland with the youth actors program \"The Pickwick Players\", initially doing musical theatre.<ref name=mediablvd>{{cite web|author=Christina Radish|title=Jackson Rathbone in Twilight|url=http://www.mediablvd.com/magazine/jackson-rathbone-in-twilight_200811143245.html|publisher=MediaBlvd Magazine|date=2008-11-14|accessdate=2008-11-14}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> For his junior and senior years of high school, Rathbone attended the [[Interlochen Center for the Arts|Interlochen Arts Academy]], a private school for the arts in [[Michigan]], where he majored in acting.<ref name=\"bio\"/><ref name=mediablvd/> After graduation, he had planned to go to the [[Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama]], but after being rejected went instead to Los Angeles to experiment with film acting and to look for work.<ref name=\"bio\"/>\n\n==Career==\nAfter being in Los Angeles for a short time, Rathbone was cast in ''[[Disney 411]]'', where he interviewed up-and-coming personalities like [[Hilary Duff]] and the sister duo [[Aly & AJ]]. He also had guest roles on ''[[The O.C.]]'' and ''[[Close to Home (2005 TV series)|Close to Home]]''. His film roles include work in ''Molding Clay'', ''[[Pray for Morning]]'', and ''Travis and Henry''. In 2005, he got the role of Nicholas Fiske in ABC Family's original series ''[[Beautiful People (US TV series)|Beautiful People]]''. In a 2008 interview, he stated it was his first leading role and was his most difficult role to fit into.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://jackson-rathbone.com/interview.php |title=Jackson Rathbone Online Interview |publisher=Jackson-rathbone.com |accessdate=2011-07-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110713073547/http://jackson-rathbone.com/interview.php |archive-date=2011-07-13 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Rathbone also played a role in ''[[Criminal Minds]]'' as Adam and Amanda.\n\nIn 2008, he played [[Jasper Hale]] in the film [[Twilight (2008 film)|''Twilight'']], based on the best-selling novel by [[Stephenie Meyer]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stepheniemeyer.com/twilight_movie.html |title=Movies &#124; Twilight |publisher=StephenieMeyer.com |date= |accessdate=2012-11-02}}</ref> He reprised his role in the sequels to ''Twilight'', ''[[The Twilight Saga: New Moon]]'', ''[[The Twilight Saga: Eclipse]]'' and ''[[The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn \u2013 Part 1]]'' and [[The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn \u2013 Part 2|''Part 2'']].<ref>{{cite web|author=Larry Carroll|title=Jackson Rathbone Thinks 'New Moon' Will Be 'Pretty Fantastic'| url=http://www.mtv.com/movies/news/articles/1602356/story.jhtml|publisher=[[MTV]]|date=2009-01-09| accessdate=2009-03-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Peter Facinelli, Ashley Greene, Kellan Lutz, Jackson Rathbone, Elizabeth Reaser, Nikki Reed, and Billy Burke Sign on to BREAKING DAWN; Plus Three New TWILIGHT: ECLIPSE Posters|url=http://www.collider.com/tag/the-twilight-saga-breaking-dawn/|publisher=Collider |date=2010-05-19 |accessdate=2010-05-20 }}</ref> In 2009, Rathbone played Jeremy in ''[[S. Darko]]''. In addition to that role, he won kudos for his performance as a serial killer on ''[[Criminal Minds]]''. Rathbone played the role of [[Sokka]] in ''[[The Last Airbender]]'', a 2010 film based on [[Avatar: The Last Airbender|the animated series.]]<ref name=\"Larry Carroll\">{{cite news|author=Larry Carroll|title='Twilight' Star Jackson Rathbone Hopes To 'Show His Range' In 'Last Airbender' |url=http://www.mtv.com/movies/news/articles/1602757/story.jhtml|publisher=MTV|date=2009-01-15| accessdate=2009-01-15 }}</ref> Though the film was a commercial hit, it was universally panned by critics, particularly for Rathbone, a [[Cultural appropriation|white actor, playing the role]] of an originally [[Circumpolar peoples|Inuit]] character.\n\n[[File:JacksonRathboneJodiePlatz.jpg|thumb|right|upright|Rathbone performing with band [[100 Monkeys]] in Indianapolis, 2011]]\n\nRathbone formerly performed in a funk band called [[100 Monkeys]] with two friends whom he met in high school at Interlochen Arts Academy, Ben Graupner and Ben Johnson,<ref name=mediablvd/> as well as close friends Jerad Anderson and M. Lawrence Abrams (\"Uncle Larry\").<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.myspace.com/these100monkeys |title=100 Monkeys &#124; Gratis muziek, tourneedata, foto's, video's |publisher=Myspace.com |date= |accessdate=2011-07-24}}</ref> Jackson plays the guitar, bass, drums, keyboard, mandolin, trumpet, harmonica and is on vocals. The band released three albums in 2009.<ref>{{cite web| author=Larry Carroll|title='Twilight' Star Jackson Rathbone Moves Beyond Jasper Hale With 100 Monkeys| \nurl=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1602653/20090113/story.jhtml|publisher=MTV|date=2009-01-13|accessdate=2009-02-26}}</ref> In December 2009, 100 Monkeys began a 100-city tour that took them to nearly every state in the US by mid-2010.<ref name=\"news-shows\">[http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/news-shows/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714023855/http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/news-shows/ |date=July 14, 2011 }}</ref> The band continued to tour into 2011 to coincide with the release of their new album, ''Liquid Zoo'', which was released in June.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/news-shows/ |title=news & shows \u00ab Official Band Website &#124; 100 Monkeys |publisher=100monkeysmusic.com |accessdate=2011-07-24 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110714023855/http://www.100monkeysmusic.com/news-shows/ |archivedate=July 14, 2011 }}</ref> The band headed overseas for their first international dates in winter 2011.<ref name=\"news-shows\"/>\n\nRathbone appeared in an episode of ''[[No Ordinary Family]]'' on November 9, 2010.<ref>[http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/11/08/can-a-live-twitter-chat-help-no-ordinary-family-ratings/71209 tvbythenumbers.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101110005020/http://tvbythenumbers.com/2010/11/08/can-a-live-twitter-chat-help-no-ordinary-family-ratings/71209 |date=2010-11-10 }} Can A Live Twitter Chat Help No Ordinary Family Ratings?</ref><ref>[http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/Movies/2010/10/25/Cybill-Shepherd-to-guest-star-on-Family/UPI-64571288054262/ www.upi.com] Cybill Shepherd to guest star on 'Family'</ref> In November 2010, it was reported he had been cast in the [[Warner Premiere]] and [[Dolphin Entertainment]] action comedy web series ''Aim High'' alongside [[Aimee Teegarden]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kit|first=Borys|title=McG-Produced Digital Series 'Aim High' Gets a Cast|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/blogs/heat-vision/mcg-produced-digital-series-aim-49664|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=February 28, 2012|date=November 29, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Van Pelt|first=Doug|title=New tv series \u2013 Aim High|url=http://www.hmmagazine.com/2010/11/new-tv-series-aim-high/|work=HM Magazine|accessdate=August 16, 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101204053603/http://www.hmmagazine.com/2010/11/new-tv-series-aim-high|archivedate=December 4, 2010}}</ref> The show in which he portrays Nick Green, a high school junior who's just starting a new school year as one of the country's 64 highly trained teenage operatives, premiered on October 18, 2011, on [[Facebook]] being the first \"social series\" ever created.<ref>{{cite web|last=Shaw|first=Lucas|title=Warner Bros. Creates First 'Social Series' for Facebook|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/29/idUS327150308420110929|work=Reuters|accessdate=February 28, 2012|date=September 29, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2011, Rathbone began shooting ''[[Live at the Foxes Den]]'', a film in which he plays the lead role of lawyer Bobby Kelly. In November 2014, Rathbone joined the cast of ''[[Pali Road]]''. Rathbone has a production company, PatchMo Entertainment, and a record company, Happy Jack Records.\n\n==Personal life==\nRathbone resides in Austin, TX and enjoys music, writing, singing and producing.<ref name=\"bio\"/> \n\nRathbone and his then girlfriend, Sheila Hafsadi, had a son, Monroe Jackson Rathbone VI, on July 5, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gossipcop.com/jackson-rathbone-baby-son-monroe-girlfriend-sheila-hafsadi/ |title=Jackson Rathbone of Twilight & Girlfriend Sheila Hafsadi Welcome Baby Boy! |publisher=Gossipcop.com |date=2012-07-05 |accessdate=2012-11-02}}</ref> Close friend and ''Twilight'' co-star [[Nikki Reed]] is the godmother. He and Hafsadi married on September 29, 2013.<ref name=\"a\">{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20740905,00.html|title=Jackson Rathbone Marries Sheila Hafsadi|publisher=people.com |date=2013-10-01 |accessdate=2013-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usmagazine.com/celebrity-news/news/jackson-rathbone-marries-sheila-hafsadi-2013110|title=Jackson Rathbone Marries Sheila Hafsadi!|publisher=usmagazine.com|date=2013-10-01 |accessdate=2013-10-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/465497/twilight-s-jackson-rathbone-marries-sheila-hafsadi|title=Twilight's Jackson Rathbone Marries Sheila Hafsadi!|publisher=eonline.com|date=2013-10-01 |accessdate=2013-10-02}}</ref> On May 31, 2016, he and Hafsadi welcomed their second child, a daughter named Presley Bowie Rathbone.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2016/05/31/jackson-rathbone-welcomes-daughter-presley-bowie/|title=Jackson Rathbone Welcomes Daughter Presley Bowie|magazine=People.com|author=Juneau, Jen and Leon, Anya|date=May 31, 2016|accessdate=September 4, 2017}}</ref> The couple were expecting a third child in late 2019. On December 31st they welcome their third child a son named Felix Valleau Rathbone.\nOn September 18, 2014, Rathbone was on board [[JetBlue]] Flight 1416 en route from [[Long Beach, California]] to [[Austin, Texas]] when its engine exploded. The plane returned to Long Beach and made an emergency landing. There were four injuries, but all passengers survived.<ref>http://www.cnn.com/2014/09/18/us/jetblue-emergency-landing/index.html</ref><ref>[http://www.latimes.com/entertainment/gossip/la-et-mg-jackson-rathbone-jetblue-emergency-landing-twilight-20140918-story.html \"Jackson Rathbone live-blogs emergency landing of his JetBlue plane\"] ''Los Angeles Times\". Retrieved 2015-6-30.</ref>\n\n===Philanthropy===\nRathbone is an honorary board member for [[Little Kids Rock]], a national nonprofit that works to restore and revitalize music education in disadvantaged U.S. public schools. He has shown support for the organization in several ways, including donating a signed ''Twilight'' script for auction, visiting a Little Kids Rock classroom, and delivering instruments to students.<ref>http://www.littlekidsrock.org/friends/our-big-fans/jackson-rathbone/ {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140114081040/http://www.littlekidsrock.org/friends/our-big-fans/jackson-rathbone/ |date=2014-01-14 }} Retrieved January 13, 2014</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[River's End (2005 film)|River's End]]'' \n| Jimmy \n|\n|-\n| 2006 \n| ''[[Pray for Morning]]'' \n| Connor \n|\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Big Stan]]'' \n| Robbie the Hippie \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |2008\n| ''Senior Skip Day'' \n| Snippy \n| Direct to video\n|-\n| ''[[Twilight (2008 film)|Twilight]]\n|[[Jasper Hale]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |2009\n| ''[[S. Darko]]'' \n| Jeremy Frame \n| Direct to video\n|-\n| ''[[Dread (film)|Dread]]'' \n| Stephen Grace \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Hurt (2009 film)|Hurt]]'' \n| Conrad Coltrane \n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Twilight Saga: New Moon]]'' \n| rowspan=\"2\"| Jasper Hale \n|\n|-\n| rowspan=4 |2010\n| ''[[The Twilight Saga: Eclipse]]'' \n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Last Airbender]]'' \n| [[Sokka]] \n|\n|-\n| ''[[Girlfriend (2010 film)|Girlfriend]]'' \n| Russ \n| \n|-\n| ''Young Again''\n| Adult Ethan\n| Short film\n|-\n| rowspan=2 |2011\n| ''100 Monkeys: Modern Time''\n| Red \n| Short film\n|-\n| ''[[The Twilight Saga: Breaking Dawn - Part 1]]''\n| Jasper Hale \n|\n